<br>
It looked extremely rocky for the Whispering Scythe that day;<br>
The froglocks had us outnumbered 2 to 1 with but a bubble of health to pay.<br>
So, when Hicm died by fire, and Senader did the same,<br>
A pallor wreathed the features of the guildmates of the game.<br>
<br>
A straggling few frogs got killed, leaving there the rest,<br>
With that hope which springs eternal within the elven breast.<br>
For they thought: &quot;If only Querkus could get an evac real fast,&quot;<br>
They'd put even plat now, with Querkus at the cast.<br>
<br>
But the Shin Lord was on Querkus and likewise was another,<br>
And third was a pounding on the druid like a mother.<br>
So that stricken multitude in a deathlike silence fought;<br>
For there seemed but little chance of Querkus not getting caught.<br>
<br>
But Hikanur let drive a crit, to the wonderment of all.<br>
And the much-loved Eimi did a roundhouse that made one fall.<br>
And when the dust had lifted, and they saw what had occurred,<br>
There was Giligan successfully mezzing a third..<br>
<br>
Then from the gladdened multitude went up a joyous yell--<br>
It rumbled in the mountaintops, it rattled in the dell;<br>
It struck upon the hillside and rebounded on the back;<br>
For Querkus, mighty Querkus was casting an evac..<br>
<br>
There was ease in Querkus’ manner as he stepped into his place,<br>
There was pride in Querkus’ bearing and a smile on Querkus’ face;<br>
And Balomar gave him a remedy to heal his wounds real fast.<br>
No stranger in the crowd could doubt 'twas Querkus beginning to cast.&quot;<br>
<br>
From Menludarja there went up a muffled roar,<br>
Like the beating of the storm waves on the stern and distant shore.<br>
&quot;An Add! Kill the reanimated hand!&quot; shouted Menlu on the stand;<br>
And it's likely he’d have interrupted Querkus had Erostle not taunted the hand.<br>
<br>
With a smile of Tunarian charity great Querkus’ visage shone;<br>
He stilled the rising tumult, he made the cast go on;<br>
He signaled to the heavens, and once more the casting flew;<br>
But Querkus got interrupted and the Arrington said, &quot;Try cast number two.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Evac!&quot; cried Mojarda, and the echo answered &quot;Evac!&quot;<br>
As he waved his arms in casting, his guildmates covered his back;<br>
They saw his face grow stern and cold, they saw his muscles strain,<br>
And they knew that Querkus wouldn't get interrupted again.<br>
<br>
The sneer is gone from Querkus lips, his teeth are clenched in hate,<br>
He pounds with cruel vengeance his hammer upon the plate;<br>
And now Querkus begins to cast and now he lets the spell go,<br>
And now the air is shattered by the force of Querkus blow.<br>
<br>
Oh, somewhere in this favored land the sun is shining bright,<br>
The bard is playing somewhere, and somewhere hearts are light;<br>
And somewhere Elves are laughing, and somewhere gnomes shout,<br>
But there is no joy in Guk: Mighty Querkus has fizzled out.<br>
 <p><B>Menludarja Pathtaker</B><br>
Ranger of Tunare<br>
Guildleader of <A HREF="http://www.whisperingscythe.org">Whispering Scythe</A><br>Somewhere ages and ages hence: <br>
Two roads diverged in a wood, and I-- <br>
I took the one less traveled by, <br>
And that has made all the difference.<br> 

